    {
      "id": "assistant-1775056713845-0bgh8p",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Done — I prepared all 10 keyframe sidecars and added the office image as a reference in each one.\n\nI treated the room image as the primary environment reference, then kept the character references in the same priority order as each frame’s `characterIds`, so continuity should stay clean.\n\nA few creative choices I baked in:\n- **SHOT-01 / SHOT-05** stay wider and more relational, so the office layout actually reads.\n- **SHOT-02 / SHOT-04** push closer on the panda for the emotional turns.\n- **SHOT-03** keeps the psychologist calm, observant, and non-performative.\n- The prompting stays **grounded and photoreal**, not gaggy, so the joke lands through sincerity.\n\nNext move is to generate the keyframe images and review them. Since the sidecars are ready, you’ll need to run the image generation step; once those PNGs exist, I can help you evaluate them and then roll straight into the shot prompts."
    }
